    <section id="import-auto-idm276440432">
      <title>Explaining and Instructing</title>
      <para id="import-auto-idm334138960">.</para>
      <para id="import-auto-idm685655968">Accurate and clear instructions are always needed on the construction site. Poor verbal communication skills can often lead to mistakes, inefficiencies and accidents. It is therefore important that each occupation can explain and give instructions. This is becoming critical as construction projects are becoming more complex and workers come from various cultural backgrounds. At the end of this section students should be able to give instructions and explanations that are appropriate to the construction industry. Students should be able to understand symbols and diagrams. They should also be able to explain a process and report on work progress using the appropriate technical terms and working in a safe manner. </para>
      <para id="import-auto-idm697763456"/>
