    <section id="import-auto-idm679537936">
      <title>When will you finish?  </title>
      <para id="import-auto-idm284634496">It is important that construction workers can talk about work in progress. </para><section id="import-auto-idm359377280">
        <title>Talking about work progress (future simple and present perfect)</title>
        <para id="eip-461">.</para><para id="import-auto-idm325632240">A: When will you finish?</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm342907408">B: I will finish soon.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm335248096">A: Have you nearly finished.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm435835968">B: Yes, I’ve nearly finished.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm362271696">A: Has John finished?</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm477091216">B: No, he will finish later.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm435009744">A: How about Pete? Has he nearly finished?</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm695268256">B: Yes, he has finished already.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm354156880">A: Thanks.</para>
        <para id="import-auto-idm463653760">.</para>
